<http://www.w3.org/ns/r2rml#inverseExpression> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An expression that allows, at query processing time, use of index-based access to the the (underlying) relational tables, instead of simply retrieving the table rows first and then applying a filter. This property is useful for retrieval based on conditions involving subject, predicate, or object generated from logical table column(s) and involves some transformation."@en .
<http://www.w3.org/ns/r2rml#inverseExpression> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
